---
import BaseLayout from '../../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
---

<BaseLayout
  title="Agent Harness Architecture — OpenCastor"
  description="Visual reference for the OpenCastor Agent Harness — context engineering, tool execution loop, P66 safety invariants, and evolution over time."
  ogUrl="https://opencastor.com/docs/harness"
>

<main>
  <!-- ── HERO ── -->
  <section class="page-hero" style="padding-bottom:32px">
    <p class="section-label reveal">Architecture</p>
    <h1 class="reveal reveal-d1">Agent Harness<br><span class="gradient-text">Visual Reference</span></h1>
    <p class="reveal reveal-d2" style="font-size:1.1rem;max-width:560px;margin:0 auto 24px">
      The harness is the OS around the model — context curation, tool execution, safety enforcement,
      and trajectory capture. The model is the CPU; the harness is everything else.
    </p>
    <div class="hero-actions reveal reveal-d3">
      <a href="#current" class="btn btn-primary">Current Architecture</a>
      <a href="#p66" class="btn btn-secondary">P66 Safety Flow</a>
      <a href="#evolution" class="btn btn-secondary">Evolution Timeline</a>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- ── Phil Schmid definition ── -->
  <section class="section" style="padding-top:0;padding-bottom:24px">
    <div class="container">
      <div class="wizard-tip reveal" style="max-width:760px;margin:0 auto">
        <strong>Definition (Phil Schmid):</strong> The harness is not the agent — it's the infrastructure
        <em>around</em> the agent. Model = CPU. Context window = RAM.
        Harness = OS. Agent = Application.<br>
        The harness provides: context engineering, tool dispatch, lifecycle hooks, planning,
        sub-agent management. It must be lightweight and build-to-delete as models improve.
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- ── DIAGRAM 1: Current architecture ── -->
  <section class="section" id="current">
    <div class="container">
      <div class="section-header reveal">
        <p class="section-label">Diagram 1</p>
        <h2 class="section-title">Current Architecture</h2>
        <p class="section-desc">Full request path from user input to response — v2026.3.20.2+</p>
      </div>

      <div class="mermaid-card reveal">
        <div class="mermaid-header">
          <span class="mermaid-label">opencastor/castor/harness.py · context.py · trajectory.py</span>
          <span class="mermaid-version">v2026.3.20.2+</span>
        </div>
        <div class="mermaid">
flowchart TD
    A["User / App / RCAN peer"] --> B["/api/command"]
    B --> C["AgentHarness.run()"]
    C --> ESTOP{"ESTOP?"}
    ESTOP -->|"YES - P66 absolute"| STOP["Stop immediately<br/>No context, hooks, or log"]
    ESTOP -->|NO| CB["ContextBuilder.build()"]

    subgraph CTX [Context Window]
        CB --> CW["PERSONA + SKILL + MEMORY<br/>STATUS + TOOLS + HISTORY"]
    end

    CW --> PROV["Provider<br/>Gemini / Claude / Ollama"]
    PROV --> LOOP["Tool Loop<br/>up to max_iterations"]

    subgraph HOOKS [Lifecycle Hooks]
        LOOP --> H1["P66AuditHook<br/>consent gate"]
        LOOP --> H2["DriftDetectionHook<br/>Jaccard 0.15"]
        LOOP --> H3[RetryOnErrorHook]
    end

    H1 --> TRAJ["TrajectoryLogger<br/>SQLite"]
    H2 --> TRAJ
    H3 --> TRAJ
    TRAJ --> RESP[Response]

    style STOP fill:#ef4444,color:#fff,stroke:#dc2626
    style ESTOP fill:#fef2f2,stroke:#fca5a5
    style CTX fill:#f0f9ff,stroke:#bae6fd
    style HOOKS fill:#fefce8,stroke:#fef08a
        </div>
      </div>

      <!-- Key files table -->
      <div class="reveal" style="max-width:760px;margin:32px auto 0">
        <table class="arch-table">
          <thead><tr><th>File</th><th>Role</th><th>Key class</th></tr></thead>
          <tbody>
            <tr><td><code>castor/harness.py</code></td><td>Orchestrator + hooks</td><td><code>AgentHarness</code>, <code>P66AuditHook</code>, <code>DriftDetectionHook</code></td></tr>
            <tr><td><code>castor/context.py</code></td><td>Context window assembly</td><td><code>ContextBuilder</code>, <code>BuiltContext</code></td></tr>
            <tr><td><code>castor/trajectory.py</code></td><td>Trajectory capture (SQLite)</td><td><code>TrajectoryLogger</code>, <code>TrajectoryRecord</code></td></tr>
            <tr><td><code>castor/dual_model.py</code></td><td>Secondary model (safety oracle, verifier)</td><td><code>DualModelHarness</code>, <code>SafetyVerdict</code></td></tr>
            <tr><td><code>castor/skills/loader.py</code></td><td>Skill matching</td><td><code>SkillLoader</code>, <code>SkillSelector</code></td></tr>
            <tr><td><code>castor/agent_tools.py</code></td><td>5 built-in agent tools</td><td><code>register_agent_tools()</code></td></tr>
          </tbody>
        </table>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- ── DIAGRAM 2: P66 safety flow ── -->
  <section class="section alt-section" id="p66">
    <div class="container">
      <div class="section-header reveal">
        <p class="section-label">Diagram 2</p>
        <h2 class="section-title">P66 Safety Invariants</h2>
        <p class="section-desc">Protocol 66 defines hard constraints that the harness enforces regardless of model output.
          ESTOP is absolute — it bypasses every other step.</p>
      </div>

      <div class="mermaid-card reveal">
        <div class="mermaid-header">
          <span class="mermaid-label">opencastor/castor/harness.py · P66AuditHook</span>
          <span class="mermaid-version">Non-negotiable invariants</span>
        </div>
        <div class="mermaid">
flowchart TD
    CMD["Incoming command"] --> E1{"ESTOP?"}
    E1 -->|YES| BYPASS["Immediate stop\nBypasses all hooks, context, log"]
    E1 -->|NO| E2{"Physical tool?"}
    E2 -->|YES| E3{"Consent granted?"}
    E3 -->|NO| BLOCK["Blocked\nBot sends ask-first message"]
    E3 -->|YES| E4{"LoA sufficient?"}
    E4 -->|NO| LOA["Blocked\nEscalation required"]
    E4 -->|YES| AUDIT["Execute\nAudit record written"]
    E2 -->|NO| EXEC["Execute normally\nNo physical gate"]

    style BYPASS fill:#ef4444,color:#fff,stroke:#dc2626
    style BLOCK fill:#f97316,color:#fff,stroke:#ea580c
    style LOA fill:#f97316,color:#fff,stroke:#ea580c
    style AUDIT fill:#22c55e,color:#fff,stroke:#16a34a
    style EXEC fill:#22c55e,color:#fff,stroke:#16a34a
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="bento reveal" style="max-width:760px;margin:32px auto 0;grid-template-columns:1fr 1fr">
        <div class="card">
          <h3>⛔ ESTOP is absolute</h3>
          <p>Triggered by <code>scope="safety"</code> or instruction starting with <code>ESTOP</code>, <code>E-STOP</code>, <code>EMERGENCY STOP</code>, <code>STOP ALL</code>, <code>HALT</code>. No hooks, no context, no logging — just stop.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="card">
          <h3>🔒 Physical tools require consent</h3>
          <p>Any tool in <code>PHYSICAL_TOOLS</code> (move, grip, actuate) is blocked until the user explicitly consents in the current session. Consent resets on session expiry.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="card">
          <h3>📊 Scope hierarchy</h3>
          <p><code>discover(0) &lt; status(1) &lt; chat(2) &lt; control(3) &lt; safety(99)</code>. A command issued at <code>chat</code> scope cannot execute <code>control</code>-level tools.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="card">
          <h3>🧠 Model cannot self-escalate</h3>
          <p>The harness enforces scope locally. The model cannot grant itself higher scope — P66 constraints are code-level, not prompt-level.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- ── DIAGRAM 3: Evolution ── -->
  <section class="section" id="evolution">
    <div class="container">
      <div class="section-header reveal">
        <p class="section-label">Diagram 3</p>
        <h2 class="section-title">Evolution Over Time</h2>
        <p class="section-desc">Each version added one layer. The harness grew from a single function call
          to a full OS-layer in four releases.</p>
      </div>

      <div class="mermaid-card reveal">
        <div class="mermaid-header">
          <span class="mermaid-label">opencastor — harness design evolution</span>
          <span class="mermaid-version">2026-03</span>
        </div>
        <div class="mermaid">
timeline
    title OpenCastor Agent Harness Evolution
    Pre-harness : Direct think() call : No hooks : No trajectory
    v2026.3.17.3 : AgentHarness orchestrator : ContextBuilder : TrajectoryLogger : P66AuditHook
    v2026.3.17.4 : SkillSystem : SkillSelector : 5 Agent Tools : castor eval CLI
    v2026.3.17.5 : DualModelHarness : DriftDetectionHook : castor trajectory CLI
    v2026.3.17.6 : castor share/install/explore : Two-tier autoresearch
    v2026.3.20.2 : RCAN v1.8.0 100/100 : Canonical MessageType : castor contribute : Harness research pipeline
        </div>
      </div>

      <!-- Design choices callout -->
      <div class="reveal" style="max-width:760px;margin:32px auto 0">
        <div class="wizard-tip">
          <strong>Key design decisions:</strong>
          <ul style="margin:8px 0 0 0;padding-left:20px;line-height:1.8">
            <li><strong>Harness is opt-in</strong> — <code>agent.harness.enabled: false</code> by default; existing robots unaffected until config updated</li>
            <li><strong>No new packages</strong> — harness uses only stdlib + existing castor deps (SQLite, asyncio, logging)</li>
            <li><strong>Build-to-delete</strong> — each harness layer designed to be replaced as models improve; thin interfaces, no lock-in</li>
            <li><strong>Trajectory is the dataset</strong> — every run logged to SQLite enables offline analysis, eval, and autoresearch tracks D/E/F</li>
            <li><strong>Safety is code, not prompt</strong> — P66 invariants enforced at harness level; model output cannot override them</li>
          </ul>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- ── ASCII art (copy-paste friendly) ── -->
  <section class="section alt-section" id="ascii">
    <div class="container">
      <div class="section-header reveal">
        <p class="section-label">ASCII Reference</p>
        <h2 class="section-title">Terminal-friendly diagram</h2>
        <p class="section-desc">Copy-paste into docs, READMEs, or robot terminals.</p>
      </div>

      <div class="code-block reveal" style="max-width:760px;margin:0 auto">
        <div class="code-header">
          <div class="code-dots"><span></span><span></span><span></span></div>
          <span class="code-filename">OpenCastor Agent Harness — ASCII</span>
          <button class="copy-btn" onclick="copyAscii(this)">Copy</button>
        </div>
        <pre class="code-body" id="ascii-art" style="white-space:pre;overflow-x:auto;font-size:0.75rem;line-height:1.5">
┌─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐
│                  OpenCastor Agent Harness                       │
│                      v2026.3.20.2+                             │
└─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘

User / App / RCAN peer
        │
        ▼
 ┌─────────────────┐
 │  /api/command   │
 └────────┬────────┘
          │
          ▼
 ┌─────────────────────────────────────────────┐
 │            AgentHarness.run()               │
 │                                             │
 │  1. ESTOP check ──────── scope=safety?      │
 │     └── YES → ⛔ bypass ALL, stop now       │
 │     └── NO  → continue                     │
 │                                             │
 │  2. ContextBuilder.build()                  │
 │     ├── PERSONA   (robot identity)          │
 │     ├── SKILL     (SkillSelector match)     │
 │     ├── MEMORY    (episodic RAG, k=3)       │
 │     ├── STATUS    (telemetry snapshot)      │
 │     ├── TOOLS     (ToolRegistry schemas)    │
 │     └── HISTORY   (last N turns, compacted) │
 │                                             │
 │  3. Provider.think_with_tools()             │
 │     └── Gemini / Claude / Ollama / HF       │
 │                                             │
 │  4. Tool Loop  (max_iterations)             │
 │     ├── P66AuditHook   (consent gate)       │
 │     ├── DriftDetection (Jaccard, 0.15)      │
 │     └── RetryOnError                        │
 │                                             │
 │  5. TrajectoryLogger → SQLite               │
 │     └── ~/.config/opencastor/trajectories.db│
 └─────────────────────────────────────────────┘
          │
          ▼
      Response

P66 Physical Tool Gate:
  physical tool called?
    └── NO  → execute normally
    └── YES → consent granted this session?
                └── NO  → 🚫 blocked, ask first
                └── YES → LoA sufficient?
                            └── NO  → 🚫 escalate
                            └── YES → ✓ execute + audit

Scope: discover(0) &lt; status(1) &lt; chat(2) &lt; control(3) &lt; safety(99)
ESTOP: absolute — bypasses context, hooks, tools, logging
        </pre>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- ── Config reference ── -->
  <section class="section" id="config">
    <div class="container">
      <div class="section-header reveal">
        <p class="section-label">Configuration</p>
        <h2 class="section-title">Enable the harness</h2>
        <p class="section-desc">The harness is opt-in. Add this block to your RCAN yaml.</p>
      </div>

      <div class="code-block reveal" style="max-width:760px;margin:0 auto">
        <div class="code-header">
          <div class="code-dots"><span></span><span></span><span></span></div>
          <span class="code-filename">robot.rcan.yaml — RCAN v1.8 canonical (100/100 conformance)</span>
          <a href="https://github.com/craigm26/OpenCastor/blob/main/config/arm.rcan.yaml" class="copy-btn" target="_blank" rel="noopener">View on GitHub →</a>
        </div>
        <div class="code-body">
<span class="k">rcan_version</span>: <span class="s">'1.6'</span>

<span class="k">metadata</span>:
  <span class="k">robot_name</span>: MyRobot
  <span class="k">robot_uuid</span>: <span class="s">00000000-0000-4000-8000-000000000001</span>
  <span class="k">description</span>: <span class="s">RCAN v1.8 full-conformance config</span>
  <span class="k">author</span>: your-github-handle
  <span class="k">license</span>: <span class="s">Apache-2.0</span>
  <span class="k">rrn</span>: <span class="s">RRN-000000000001</span>
  <span class="k">rrn_uri</span>: <span class="s">rrn://you/robot/opencastor/my-robot-001</span>

<span class="k">agent</span>:
  <span class="k">provider</span>: google
  <span class="k">model</span>: gemini-2.0-flash
  <span class="k">vision_enabled</span>: <span class="s">true</span>
  <span class="k">safety_stop</span>: <span class="s">true</span>
  <span class="k">latency_budget_ms</span>: <span class="s">3000</span>
  <span class="k">offline_provider</span>: ollama
  <span class="k">confidence_gates</span>:
    - <span class="k">scope</span>: control
      <span class="k">min_confidence</span>: <span class="s">0.75</span>
      <span class="k">on_fail</span>: block
    - <span class="k">scope</span>: safety
      <span class="k">min_confidence</span>: <span class="s">0.90</span>
      <span class="k">on_fail</span>: block

<span class="k">tiered_brain</span>:
  <span class="k">fast_provider</span>: ollama
  <span class="k">fast_model</span>: gemma3:1b         <span class="cm"># handles status / quick nav</span>
  <span class="k">slow_provider</span>: google
  <span class="k">slow_model</span>: gemini-2.0-flash   <span class="cm"># handles complex reasoning + vision</span>
  <span class="k">planner_interval</span>: <span class="s">10</span>

<span class="k">safety</span>:
  <span class="k">local_safety_wins</span>: <span class="s">true</span>
  <span class="k">emergency_stop_distance</span>: <span class="s">0.4</span>
  <span class="k">estop_bypass_rate_limit</span>: <span class="s">true</span>
  <span class="k">watchdog</span>:
    <span class="k">timeout_s</span>: <span class="s">10</span>

<span class="k">hardware_safety</span>:
  <span class="k">physical_estop</span>: <span class="s">false</span>
  <span class="k">hardware_watchdog_mcu</span>: <span class="s">false</span>

<span class="k">p66</span>:
  <span class="k">enabled</span>: <span class="s">true</span>
  <span class="k">loa_enforcement</span>: <span class="s">true</span>
  <span class="k">consent_required</span>: <span class="s">true</span>
  <span class="k">manifest</span>:
    <span class="k">estop_qos_bypass</span>: <span class="s">true</span>

<span class="k">consent</span>:
  <span class="k">required</span>: <span class="s">true</span>
  <span class="k">mode</span>: explicit
  <span class="k">scope_threshold</span>: control

<span class="k">security</span>:
  <span class="k">replay_protection</span>:
    <span class="k">enabled</span>: <span class="s">true</span>
    <span class="k">window_s</span>: <span class="s">30</span>
  <span class="k">signing</span>:
    <span class="k">enabled</span>: <span class="s">false</span>
    <span class="k">algorithm</span>: Ed25519

<span class="k">loa</span>:
  <span class="k">enforcement</span>: <span class="s">true</span>
  <span class="k">min_loa_for_control</span>: <span class="s">1</span>

<span class="k">geofence</span>:
  <span class="k">enabled</span>: <span class="s">false</span>
  <span class="k">boundary</span>:
    <span class="k">type</span>: none

<span class="k">transport</span>:
  <span class="k">supported</span>: [http, mqtt]
  <span class="k">constrained_enabled</span>: <span class="s">false</span>

<span class="k">multimodal</span>:
  <span class="k">enabled</span>: <span class="s">true</span>
  <span class="k">max_chunk_bytes</span>: <span class="s">1048576</span>

<span class="k">offline</span>:
  <span class="k">enabled</span>: <span class="s">true</span>
  <span class="k">fallback_provider</span>: ollama

<span class="k">federation</span>:
  <span class="k">enabled</span>: <span class="s">true</span>
  <span class="k">consent_bridge</span>: <span class="s">false</span>

<span class="k">r2ram</span>:
  <span class="k">scopes</span>: [discover, status, chat, control, safety]

<span class="k">network</span>:
  <span class="k">allow_remote_override</span>: <span class="s">false</span>

<span class="k">rcan_protocol</span>:
  <span class="k">port</span>: <span class="s">8000</span>
  <span class="k">capabilities</span>: [status, nav, teleop, chat]
  <span class="k">enable_mdns</span>: <span class="s">true</span>
  <span class="k">enable_jwt</span>: <span class="s">false</span>

<span class="k">cloud</span>:
  <span class="k">firebase_project</span>: opencastor
  <span class="k">gateway_url</span>: <span class="s">http://127.0.0.1:8000</span>
  <span class="k">telemetry_interval_s</span>: <span class="s">30</span>
  <span class="k">poll_interval_s</span>: <span class="s">5</span>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- ── Default harness config ── -->
  <section class="section alt-section" id="default-harness">
    <div class="container">
      <div class="section-header reveal">
        <p class="section-label">Default Config</p>
        <h2 class="section-title">Canonical Default Harness</h2>
        <p class="section-desc">
          This is the default harness. It is automatically updated when the autoresearch pipeline finds a better configuration.
          Source: <code>castor/harness/default_harness.yaml</code>
        </p>
      </div>

      <div class="code-block reveal" style="max-width:760px;margin:0 auto">
        <div class="code-header">
          <div class="code-dots"><span></span><span></span><span></span></div>
          <span class="code-filename">castor/harness/default_harness.yaml</span>
          <a href="https://github.com/craigm26/OpenCastor/blob/main/castor/harness/default_harness.yaml" class="copy-btn" target="_blank" rel="noopener">View on GitHub &rarr;</a>
        </div>
        <pre class="code-body" style="white-space:pre;overflow-x:auto;font-size:0.75rem;line-height:1.5">
<span class="k">harness</span>:
  <span class="k">enabled</span>: <span class="s">true</span>
  <span class="k">max_iterations</span>: <span class="s">6</span>
  <span class="k">thinking_budget</span>: <span class="s">1024</span>
  <span class="k">context_budget</span>: <span class="s">8192</span>
  <span class="k">p66_consent_threshold</span>: physical
  <span class="k">retry_on_error</span>: <span class="s">true</span>
  <span class="k">drift_detection</span>: <span class="s">true</span>
  <span class="k">cost_gate_usd</span>: <span class="s">0.05</span>

  <span class="k">layers</span>:
    <span class="cm"># ── ALWAYS-ON SAFETY INVARIANTS ──</span>
    - <span class="k">id</span>: hook-p66
      <span class="k">type</span>: hook
      <span class="k">label</span>: P66 Safety
      <span class="k">enabled</span>: <span class="s">true</span>
      <span class="k">can_disable</span>: <span class="s">false</span>
      <span class="k">config</span>: &#123; <span class="k">p66_audit</span>: <span class="s">true</span> &#125;

    <span class="cm"># ── SECURITY & VALIDATION ──</span>
    - <span class="k">id</span>: prompt-guard
      <span class="k">type</span>: guard
      <span class="k">label</span>: Prompt Guard
      <span class="k">enabled</span>: <span class="s">true</span>
      <span class="k">config</span>: &#123; <span class="k">block_jailbreak</span>: <span class="s">true</span>, <span class="k">risk_threshold</span>: <span class="s">0.6</span> &#125;

    <span class="cm"># ── CONTEXT ASSEMBLY ──</span>
    - <span class="k">id</span>: context-builder
      <span class="k">type</span>: context
      <span class="k">label</span>: Context Builder
      <span class="k">enabled</span>: <span class="s">true</span>
      <span class="k">can_disable</span>: <span class="s">false</span>
      <span class="k">config</span>: &#123; <span class="k">memory</span>: <span class="s">true</span>, <span class="k">telemetry</span>: <span class="s">true</span>, <span class="k">system_prompt</span>: <span class="s">true</span>, <span class="k">skills_context</span>: <span class="s">true</span>, <span class="k">rcan_identity</span>: <span class="s">true</span> &#125;

    <span class="cm"># ── WORKING MEMORY ──</span>
    - <span class="k">id</span>: working-memory
      <span class="k">type</span>: memory
      <span class="k">label</span>: Working Memory
      <span class="k">config</span>: &#123; <span class="k">max_entries</span>: <span class="s">50</span>, <span class="k">ttl_s</span>: <span class="s">1800</span>, <span class="k">persist</span>: <span class="s">false</span> &#125;

    <span class="cm"># ── SKILLS ──</span>
    - <span class="k">id</span>: skill-navigate-to         <span class="cm"># order: 0, enabled</span>
    - <span class="k">id</span>: skill-camera-describe      <span class="cm"># order: 1, enabled</span>
    - <span class="k">id</span>: skill-web-lookup           <span class="cm"># order: 2, enabled</span>
    - <span class="k">id</span>: skill-arm-manipulate       <span class="cm"># order: 3, disabled by default</span>
    - <span class="k">id</span>: skill-peer-coordinate      <span class="cm"># order: 4, disabled by default</span>

    <span class="cm"># ── CONFIDENCE & SAFETY GATES ──</span>
    - <span class="k">id</span>: circuit-breaker
